'''Petr Málek''' ({{IPA-cs|ˈpɛtr̩ ˈmaːlɛk}}; 26 November 1961 – 30 November 2019) <ref>https://www.idnes.cz/sport/ostatni/zemrel-petr-malek-olympijsky-medailista-ve-skeetu.A191130_174535_sporty_ten</ref> was a [[Czech Republic|Czech]] sport shooter, born in [[Moravský Krumlov]]. He won the Silver Medal in skeet at the Sydney [[2000 Olympic Games]].<ref>[https://www.sports-reference.com/olympics/athletes/ma/petr-malek-1.html Olympic results]</ref> He was Cyprus coach 2002–2008 and later a private coach. He died in [[Kuwait]], aged 58.

